hr.fer.zemris.ml.training.decision_tree

Class CARTGenerator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.ml.training.decision_tree.CARTGenerator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the target value, usually String for classification and Double for function approximation tasks.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITreeGenerator<T>

    public class CARTGenerator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ITreeGenerator<T>
    Decision tree generator based on CART algorithm. Supports only features whose values are continuous (double).

    User can specify which split evaluation criterion, which terminal node factory and which parameters will be used.

    Author:
    Dan

        splitCriterion - criterion to evaluate the best possible split at the current node
        factory - terminal node factory
        maxDepth - max tree depth
        numOfFeatures - number of features all training samples have
        featuresToCheck - number of features to randomly choose at each node that will be considered for splitting the current samples
